task.summary:
BLPHNX11 - TableView Updates in Real Time
-Added the ability to see character names -Added local time when events happen -Added what continent kills occured -Added if an event type is a kill or death

BLPHX11 - Added new features to KillBoard Tab
-Added faction colors for character names -API calls happen before updating the table view instead of during -Added 6 Labels to indicate statistics in the tableView -Moved static words into the resource bundle -The GUI and backend can now work independently

BLPHX20 - Added Vehicles names
-Vehicle ID's now display the vehicle name in the Table View -Columns have max Widths so that they don't take too much space -Dates have been formated to yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss -Small fixes to ensure that Id's aren't being called more than once in a Service

BLPHNX23 - Fixed Small Issues, Cleaned up code
-Added valuable comments -Re-aligned components of the GUI -Added a background color for extra info on the killboard -Removed isHeadshot from casualty Display, since its not being used as a column -Moved words into the resource bundle (Suicide, Unknown) -Played with the progress bar to better show how much time is left before the application displays the content -Fixed the max and min width of columns so that the table view looks good in as many GUI sizes as possible
